{
  "id": "selective_clear_removes_keys",
  "description": "`cookieJar: \"selective_clear\"` with `clearCookies: [\"sessionId\"]` removes only that key from the default jar before the call; any other previously stored cookies remain and are sent (spec \u00a73.3, \u00a715.6). Call 0 primes the jar with sessionId=abc and other=keep via two Set-Cookie headers. Call 1 selectively clears sessionId \u2014 the outgoing Cookie header carries only `other=keep`.",
  "spec_refs": [
    "lace-spec.md \u00a73.3",
    "lace-spec.md \u00a715.6"
  ],
  "type": "execute",
  "input": {
    "source": "get(\"http://127.0.0.1:{port}/prime\").expect(status: 200)\nget(\"http://127.0.0.1:{port}/after\", { cookieJar: \"selective_clear\", clearCookies: [\"sessionId\"] }).expect(status: 200)\n",
